  m_Name: Female_dialogue1
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  dialogueInfo:
  - dialogue: But Rehoboam rejected the advice of the elders; instead, he consulted
      the young men who had grown up with him and served him.
  - dialogue: "He asked them, \u201CWhat message do you advise that we send back
      to these people who have spoken to me, saying, \u2018Lighten the yoke your
      father put on us\u2019?\u201D"
  - dialogue: "The young men who had grown up with him replied, \u201CThis is how
      you should answer these people who said to you, \u2018Your father made our
      yoke heavy, but you must make it lighter.\u2019 This is what you should tell
      them: \u2018My little finger is thicker than my father\u2019s waist!"
